707420f-a.title: Brooklyn: Willow St. - Clark St.
707420f-a.text:
98-114 Willow Street, south from Clark Street, showing No. 98, at the
extreme right. The frame house in the center, No. 104, was built in 1827
and is said to be the oldest house on Brooklyn Heights.
May 1925.

707421f-a.title: Brooklyn: Willow St. - Clark St.
707421f-a.text:
Willow Street, east side, north from Clark Street. In the right fore-
ground was the estate of Samuel Rowland. The homes were sold in 1925.
In 1929, an apartment building occupied the site.
1925.

707427f-a.text:

the partially seen apartment house at the extreme right, formerly stood
